        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 9:21PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 920 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chavistown, or near Bennettsville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Maxton, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg, Laurel Hill, and
Bowmore.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
